[{"body": "PT Bank Negara Indonesia Tbk (BNI) has partnered with PT Bumi Siak Pusako to provide post-employment compensation fund program services, marking its commitment to providing financial solutions for workers in the country, with its pension fund management arm, DPLK BNI, currently managing IDR 32.38 trillion in funds and controlling 22.97% of the market share. The partnership aims to increase awareness and participation in pension programs, with only 12% of Indonesia's elderly population having prepared for retirement, and DPLK BNI's chairman urging the public to take retirement planning seriously.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 2, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51646/bni-bumi-siak-pusako-collaborate-employee-retirement-solutions", "sub_sector": ["banks"], "tags": ["Financial Ratios", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Fintech", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BBNI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-04T15:28:08", "title": "BNI partners with PT Bumi Siak Pusako to provide post-employment compensation fund program services to employees."}, {"body": "PT Fast Food Indonesia Tbk (FAST), the management of KFC and Taco Bell, is seeking a loan from its majority shareholders due to a capital deficiency anticipated during the expansion of outlets, with its cash and cash equivalent decreasing to IDR 87.51 billion in September 2024 from IDR 208.55 billion in December 2023. The company's total current assets also dropped to IDR 802.74 billion in January-September 2024, compared to IDR 947.54 billion in December 2023, prompting a request for working capital credit to boost sales.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51645/fast-seeks-loan-gelael-indoritel", "sub_sector": ["consumer-services"], "tags": ["Debt", "Balance Sheets", "Financial Ratios", "Executive Changes", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["FAST.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-04T15:17:58", "title": "KFC Operator in Indonesia Seeks Loan from Majority Shareholders to Support Expansion Amid Cash Shortfall."}, {"body": "The Indonesia Stock Exchange has temporarily suspended transactions for four issuers - PT Lippo General Insurance Tbk (LPGI), PT Panasia Indo Resources Tbk (HDTX), PT Metro Realty Tbk (MTSM), and PT Shield Service Tbk (SOSS) - due to their failure to meet the minimum 7.5% free float requirement, with free float shares ranging from 0.53% to 6.27% of total listed shares. The suspended issuers have a combined total of 3,144 million shares, with controllers holding significant portions of shares, and ultimate beneficial owners including Seung Youn Kim, Awong Hidjaja, PT Yakin Wiskon, and Sohgo Security Services Co, Ltd.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51644/float-requirement-unmet-idx-suspends-issuers", "sub_sector": ["insurance", "apparel-luxury-goods", "properties-real-estate"], "tags": ["IDX", "IDX Composite", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Executive Changes", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["LPGI.JK", "HDTX.JK", "MTSM.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-04T14:40:04", "title": "Indonesia Stock Exchange Temporarily Suspends Four Issuers for Failing to Meet Minimum Free Float Requirement."}, {"body": "PT XL Axiata Tbk (EXCL) shares rose 3.19% to IDR 2,260 per share despite President Director Dian Siswarini's resignation, with the company reporting a 9M 2024 net profit of IDR 1.31 trillion, up from IDR 999.9 billion in 9M 2023, driven by revenue growth from IDR 23.86 trillion to IDR 25.36 trillion. The company's plan will be decided during an extraordinary general meeting of shareholders, according to Corporate Secretary Ranty Astari Rachman.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 2, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 1}, "score": 75, "sector": "infrastructures", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51643/dian-siswarini-leave-excl-stocks-unaffected", "sub_sector": ["telecommunication"], "tags": ["IDX", "Earnings Report", "Executive Changes", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["EXCL.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-04T13:22:02", "title": "PT XL Axiata's stock price rises despite President Director Dian Siswarini's resignation."}, {"body": "The Jakarta Stock Price Composite Index (IHSG) surged 1.49% or 107.05 points to 7,303.52, driven by gains in nearly all sectors, with the basic-industry index leading the way with a 2.77% increase. The transaction volume reached 113.69 million stock lots, valued at IDR 5.64 trillion, with 10 out of 11 sectoral indices reporting uptrends, except for the tech sector which declined 0.32%.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51642/ihsg-strengthened-session-tech-sector-weakened", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["IDX Composite", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Market Sentiment", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-12-04T13:02:44", "title": "Jakarta Stock Price Composite Index Rises 1.49% to 7,303.52, Supported by Most Sectors."}, {"body": "The Indonesian insurance industry saw a significant increase in general insurance claims, reaching IDR 33.38 trillion in September 2024, up 18.5% year-on-year, leading to a jump in public insurance companies' stock prices. Among the 18 insurance industry issuers, PT MSIG Life Insurance Indonesia (MSIG) saw the highest increase of 5.86% or 425-point jump to IDR 7,675 per share, while PT Asuransi Bintang Tbk (ASBI) reported the deepest plunge of 3.67% or 20-point decline.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51636/increase-claims-insurance-companies-bullish", "sub_sector": ["insurance", "insurance"], "tags": ["IDX", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Indicators", "Mixed"], "tickers": ["LIFE.JK", "ASBI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-04T09:34:36", "title": "Indonesian insurance industry sees surge in claims and stock prices in September 2024."}, {"body": "The Indonesian government plans to invest IDR 19.08 trillion to build a methanol factory in Bojonegoro, East Java, with a production capacity of 800,000 tons per year, aiming to reduce the country's reliance on imported methanol, which currently accounts for 80% of domestic demand. The project is expected to save IDR 266.5 trillion in foreign exchange reserves by reducing crude palm oil exports, which are currently used to produce methanol.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 2, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51635/indonesia-build-methanol-factory-worth-idr", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials"], "tags": ["Energy Commodities", "Palm Oil", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2024-12-04T08:03:47", "title": "Indonesian government to build methanol factory worth IDR 19.08 trillion to reduce imports and meet local demand."}, {"body": "Foreign net buy in Indonesia reached IDR 2.08 trillion (USD 130.42 million) on Monday, the highest since September 19, 2024, with PT GoTo Gojek Tokopedia Tbk (GOTO) recording the highest foreign net buy of 1.16 billion shares. Other blue-chip stocks, including PT Barito Pacific Tbk, PT Telkom Indonesia Tbk (TLKM), and PT Bank Mandiri Tbk (BMRI), also saw significant foreign net purchases, signaling a positive trend despite it being too early to conclude a full return of foreign investors.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51634/blue-chip-stocks-inflows-foreign-outflows", "sub_sector": ["software-it-services", "basic-materials", "telecommunication", "banks"], "tags": ["IDX", "Foreign Investor", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["GOTO.JK", "BRPT.JK", "TLKM.JK", "BMRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-04T07:02:56", "title": "Foreign Net Buy Reaches Highest Level Since September 2024 with USD 130.42 Million Inflow"}, {"body": "The Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index (JCI) surged 2.11% or 149.03 points to 7,196.02, driven by the technology sector's 3.18% gain, with PT Bank Central Asia Tbk (BBCA) leading the gainers with a 4.62% increase. Foreign investors recorded a net sale of IDR 2.08 trillion, with total inflows of IDR 7.46 trillion and outflows of IDR 5.38 trillion, as the JCI rebounded from its earlier decline this week.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51633/jci-rebounded-today-foreign-reached-idr", "sub_sector": ["banks"], "tags": ["IDX Composite", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Foreign Investor", "Market Sentiment", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BBCA.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-03T20:35:56", "title": "Jakarta Composite Stock Price Index Rises 2.11% to 7,196.02 on Strong Technology Sector Performance"}, {"body": "Foreign investors bought a net 1.56 billion shares, with top purchases including 1.16 billion shares of PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia Tbk (GOTO), 198.93 million shares of PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur Tbk (ASTR), and 52.93 million shares of PT Barito Pacific Tbk (BRPT). Meanwhile, foreign investors sold a net 87 million shares of PT Bumi Resources Tbk (BUMI), 44.41 million shares of PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk (BBRI), and 30.54 million shares of PT Bank Pembangunan Daerah Banten Tbk (BBPD).", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51632/foreign-transactions-increase-foreign-volume-surplus-shares", "sub_sector": ["software-it-services", "oil-gas-coal", "basic-materials", "basic-materials", "oil-gas-coal", "banks", "banks"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["GOTO.JK", "BIPI.JK", "BRPT.JK", "BRMS.JK", "BUMI.JK", "BBRI.JK", "BEKS.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-03T18:49:11", "title": "Foreign investors in Indonesia buy 6 billion shares, led by digital company PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia Tbk, with a net surplus of 1.56 billion shares."}, {"body": "PT Elang Mahkota Teknologi Tbk (EMTK) is planning a private placement of 75 million shares, valued at IDR 32.7 billion, as part of its management employee stock option plan program, with an exercise price of IDR 436 per share. The corporate action, approved during the annual general meeting of shareholders in June 2022 and reiterated in June 2024, is scheduled to take place on December 11, 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 0, "management": 2, "ownership": 1, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51631/emtk-conduct-mesop-price-set-idr", "sub_sector": ["software-it-services"], "tags": ["Executive Changes", "Stock Splits", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["EMTK.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-03T18:00:08", "title": "PT Elang Mahkota Teknologi to issue 75 million shares for employee stock option plan worth IDR 32.7 billion."}, {"body": "PT MPX Logistics International Tbk (MPXL) has expanded its logistics services to include ocean freight, with a capital investment of IDR 5 billion, aiming to drive revenue growth, and its expedition services already contributed 49.07% of total revenue, equal to IDR 72.62 billion, from January to September 2024. Despite this, MPXL's stock has plummeted 60% since the beginning of the year, from IDR 250 per share to IDR 100 per share as of Tuesday morning.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "transportation-logistic", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51625/boosting-growth-mpxl-expand-sea-expedition-services", "sub_sector": ["logistics-deliveries"], "tags": ["IDX", "Stock Splits", "Dividends", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["MPXL.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-03T11:40:25", "title": "MPX Logistics to Expand Ocean Freight Services to Drive Revenue Growth"}, {"body": "PT Bank Negara Indonesia Tbk (BNI) recorded a 27% nominal growth in merchant transactions until October 2024, with a significant 208% growth in QRIS transactions compared to the previous year, demonstrating the bank's commitment to providing best services to its partners and customers. BNI continues to innovate with various solutions, including Wondr BNI, Android EDC, and QRIS Tap, to encourage digital payment adoption and strengthen relationships with its merchant partners.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51624/bni-connects-loyal-merchants-bni-wonderful-movie-day", "sub_sector": ["banks", "food-beverage", "oil-gas-coal", "retailing", "heavy-constructions-civil-engineering", "