.JK", "AMAN.JK", "SOTS.JK", "SMGA.JK", "CBRE.JK", "LPIN.JK", "SMLE.JK", "RBMS.JK", "DCII.JK", "IKAN.JK", "SCPI.JK", "PRIM.JK", "BEER.JK", "MTLA.JK", "POSA.JK", "TRIO.JK", "PEGE.JK", "INCI.JK", "SEMA.JK", "TNCA.JK", "GTSI.JK", "PEVE.JK", "TRIL.JK", "PNSE.JK", "IOTF.JK", "MRAT.JK", "ARKA.JK", "CHIP.JK", "YELO.JK", "PORT.JK", "MAGP.JK", "HADE.JK", "IBOS.JK", "TIRA.JK", "PSDN.JK", "MAPB.JK", "ASJT.JK", "BIPP.JK", "CTBN.JK", "VOKS.JK", "SONA.JK", "VKTR.JK", "BSML.JK", "RELF.JK", "LMPI.JK", "NEST.JK", "KBAG.JK", "DEPO.JK", "IPPE.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-03T10:25:13", "title": "BNI holds appreciation event for loyal merchants, aims to strengthen relationships and encourage digital transactions."}, {"body": "PT Delta Dunia Makmur Tbk (DGWG) is set to raise IDR 1.03 trillion from its initial public offering (IPO) of 1.66 billion shares, priced between IDR 420 and IDR 620 per share, with 54.7% of the proceeds allocated to capital boost PT Fertilizer Inti Technology. The IPO will take place from December 2 to 16, 2024, followed by public offering on December 27, and listing on the Indonesia Stock Exchange on January 10, 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 2}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51623/eyeing-idr-ipo-delta-giri-wacana-finally-debut", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["IPO", "IDX", "IDX Composite", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["DOID.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-03T08:16:47", "title": "PT Delta Giri Wacana to Raise IDR 1.03 Trillion in IPO with 1.66 Billion Shares Offered"}, {"body": "PT Sumber Alfaria Trijaya Tbk (AMRT) saw a 0.7% or 20-point climb to IDR 2,870 per share, contributing 0.90 points to the IHSG, with a transaction volume of 16.44 million shares and a foreign net buy of 3.02 million shares. Despite this, AMRT's price has plummeted 12.77% or 420 points over the past month and 0.69% or 20 points since the beginning of the year.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 1, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "consumer-non-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51622/amrt-entered-leaders-heres-investors-respond", "sub_sector": ["food-staples-retailing"], "tags": ["IDX", "IDX Composite", "Market Trends", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["AMRT.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-03T07:11:37", "title": "Alfamart's stock price surges 0.7% after being listed under top leaders of IHSG, driven by foreign net buy of 3.02 million shares."}, {"body": "Foreign investors bought a total of 402.39 million shares of Indonesian companies, with PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur TBK (no ticker) leading the pack with 278.92 million shares, followed by PT Multipolar TBK (no ticker) with 36.57 million shares, and PT Sarana Mitra Luas TBK (no ticker) with 29.13 million shares. The total transaction value reached IDR 12.76 trillion (USD 803.13 million), with foreign investors accounting for 38% of the total transactions, while domestic investors made up the remaining 62%.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/51621/stocks-favoured-foreign-investors-week", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal", "food-staples-retailing", "software-it-services", "industrial-goods"], "tags": ["Foreign Investor", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["BIPI.JK", "MLPL.JK", "MLPT.JK", "SMIL.JK"], "timestamp": "2024-12-03T06:08:27", "title": "Foreign investors snap up Indonesian stocks across various sectors, led by PT Astrindo Nusantara Infrastruktur and Lippo Group companies."}]